-- China benchmark money rate opens at lowest level since April 2013
-- 
-- Sun Mar 09, 2014 09:48PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, March 10 (Reuters) - China's benchmark seven-day bond repurchase rate opened at 2.20 percent, its lowest opening quote since April 2013, following the release of disappointing macroeconomic data this weekend. [ID:nL3N0M508C]

The People's Bank of China (PBOC) has been letting short-term money rates slide steadily, beginning in early February, which economists suspect is intended to provide more support for economic growth while simultateously discouraging hot money inflows.